<taxonomicName id="08E14D5C3669AB10FE7EFC28F276F510" authorityName="Gill" authorityYear="1861" box="[424,553,324,349]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FD95EACD3669AB10FE7EFC28F276F510" box="[424,553,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Pachypops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, despite bearing three mental barbels and six mental pores, 
<taxonomicName id="08E14D5C3669AB10FE80FC00F1B7F5C8" authorityName="Steindachner" authorityYear="1879" box="[342,488,364,390]" class="Diplopoda" family="Platyrhacidae" genus="Pachyurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adspersus">
<emphasis id="FD95EACD3669AB10FE80FC00F13AF5C8" box="[342,357,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="FD95EACD3669AB10FEA5FC00F1B7F5C8" box="[371,488,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">adspersus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks the expanded haemal spine and the appendages on the swimbladder, which occur in 
<taxonomicName id="08E14D5C3669AB10FDDFFCF8F2D5F5E0" authorityName="Gill" authorityYear="1861" box="[521,650,404,429]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FD95EACD3669AB10FDDFFCF8F2D5F5E0" box="[521,650,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Pachypops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="AB704B2E3669AB10FD48FCF8F314F5E3" author="Casatti" box="[670,843,404,430]" firstAuthor="Casatti" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="133" refId="ref9213" refString="Casatti, L. (2001) Taxonomia do genero sul-americano Pachyurus Agassiz, 1831 (Teleostei: Perciformes: Sciaenidae) e descricao de duas novas especies. Comunicacoes do Museu de Ciencias e Tecnologia da PUCRS, Serie Zoologia, 14, 133 - 178." type="journal article" year="2001">
Casatti (
<number id="792924F83669AB10FCD0FCF8F31CF5E3" box="[774,835,404,430]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="2001.0">2001</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName id="08E14D5C3669AB10FC33FCF8F422F5E0" authorityName="Steindachner" authorityYear="1879" box="[997,1149,404,430]" class="Diplopoda" family="Platyrhacidae" genus="Pachyurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adspersus">
<emphasis id="FD95EACD3669AB10FC33FCF8F3ACF5E0" box="[997,1011,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="FD95EACD3669AB10FBDEFCF8F422F5E0" box="[1032,1149,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">adspersus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a member of 
<taxonomicName id="08E14D5C3669AB10FEDEFCD0F1D9F598" authorityName="Agassiz in Spix &amp; Agassiz" authorityYear="1831" box="[264,390,444,469]" class="Diplopoda" family="Platyrhacidae" genus="Pachyurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FD95EACD3669AB10FEDEFCD0F1D9F598" box="[264,390,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Pachyurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as originally proposed by Steindachner. An expanded haemal spine on the first caudal vertebra is also present in some other examined perciforms (the haemulid 
<taxonomicName id="08E14D5C3669AB10FB1AFC88F18AF668" baseAuthorityName="Jordan &amp; Gilbert" baseAuthorityYear="1882" class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Haemulon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="steindachneri">
<emphasis id="FD95EACD3669AB10FB1AFC88F18AF668" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Haemulon steindachneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the polynemid 
<taxonomicName id="08E14D5C3669AB10FD4EFF60F3F4F668" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[664,939,524,549]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Polynemidae" genus="Polydactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="virginicus">
<emphasis id="FD95EACD3669AB10FD4EFF60F3F4F668" box="[664,939,524,549]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Polydactylus virginicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the sciaenids 
<emphasis id="FD95EACD3669AB10FB58FF60F264F600" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<taxonomicName id="08E14D5C3669AB10FB58FF60F13EF600" baseAuthorityName="Cuvier" baseAuthorityYear="1829" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Dendrophysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="russelli">Dendrophysa russelli</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="08E14D5C3669AB10FEA7FF58F264F600" baseAuthorityName="Cuvier in Cuvier &amp; Valenciennes" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[369,571,564,589]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Kathala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="axillaris">Kathala axillaris</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="08E14D5C3669AB10FD54FF58F32DF600" baseAuthorityName="Castelnau" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[642,882,564,589]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Plagioscion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="auratus">
<emphasis id="FD95EACD3669AB10FD54FF58F32DF600" box="[642,882,564,589]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Plagioscion auratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, pers. obser.) but it is interpreted as having been independently derived in these taxa.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CF5E36DF3669AB10FEEEFFE8F43FF773" blockId="3.[264,1324,284,830]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Based on the barbel morphology 
<taxonomicName id="08E14D5C3669AB10FD6BFFE8F40BF6D3" authority="Cervigon 1982" authorityName="Cervigon" authorityYear="1982" box="[701,1108,644,670]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cevegei">
<emphasis id="FD95EACD3669AB10FD6BFFE8F3C2F6D0" box="[701,925,644,669]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Pachypops cevegei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="AB704B2E3669AB10FC72FFE8F40BF6D3" author="Cervigon" box="[932,1108,644,670]" firstAuthor="Cervigon" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="205 - 260" refId="ref9261" refString="Cervigon, F. (1982) La ictiofauna estuarina del cano Manamo y areas adyacentes. In: D. Nova (Ed), Los recursos pesqueros del Rio Orinoco y su explotacion. Corporacion Venezuelana de Guayana, Division de Desarrolo Agricola, Caracas, pp. 205 - 260." type="book chapter" year="1982">
Cervigón 
<number id="792924F83669AB10FBCFFFE8F40BF6D3" box="[1049,1108,644,670]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1982.0">1982</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is not a species of 
<taxonomicName id="08E14D5C3669AB10FEDEFFC0F1D6F688" authorityName="Gill" authorityYear="1861" box="[264,393,684,709]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FD95EACD3669AB10FEDEFFC0F1D6F688" box="[264,393,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Pachypops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but instead a species of 
<taxonomicName id="08E14D5C3669AB10FD6FFFC0F334F688" authorityName="Bonaparte in Bonaparte" authorityYear="1831" box="[697,875,684,709]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Micropogonias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FD95EACD3669AB10FD6FFFC0F334F688" box="[697,875,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Micropogonias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, of six nominal species of 
<taxonomicName id="08E14D5C3669AB10FEDEFFB8F1D6F6A0" authorityName="Gill" authorityYear="1861" box="[264,393,724,749]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FD95EACD3669AB10FEDEFFB8F1D6F6A0" box="[264,393,724,749]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Pachypops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
according to previous authors, two (
<taxonomicName id="08E14D5C3669AB10FCB6FFB8F43CF6A0" baseAuthorityName="Steindachner" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[864,1123,724,749]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="adspersus">
<emphasis id="FD95EACD3669AB10FCB6FFB8F43CF6A0" box="[864,1123,724,749]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Pachypops adspersus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="08E14D5C3669AB10FB7CFFB8F13FF758" authorityName="Cervigon" authorityYear="1982" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cevegei">
<emphasis id="FD95EACD3669AB10FB7CFFB8F13FF758" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Pachypops cevegei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) are not assignable to the genus. The remaining nominal species are discussed below under “Comments” for 
<taxonomicName id="08E14D5C3669AB10FDBDFE48F30EF770" baseAuthorityName="La Cepede" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[619,849,804,829]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fourcroi">
<emphasis id="FD95EACD3669AB10FDBDFE48F30EF770" box="[619,849,804,829]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Pachypops fourcroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="08E14D5C3669AB10FC5CFE48F406F770" authorityName=", Rio Mamore" baseAuthorityName="Muller and Troschel" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[906,1113,804,829]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="trifilis">
<emphasis id="FD95EACD3669AB10FC5CFE48F406F770" box="[906,1113,804,829]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Pachypops trifilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
